The paper presents a framework for active learning using crowdsourced data to improve deep learning models. The paper focuses on the application of intent classification in Alexa, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses Bayesian deep learning, which is a popular topic in machine learning, and hence cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models for image classification, which falls under the category of computer vision (CV), making cs.CV a possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of crowdsourcing, which involves human-computer interaction, making cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of active learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI a possible sub-category.
